lenders.name: Feather & Thread
lenders.loan_because:
We loan because we know how difficult it can be to fund a start-up or expand an existing business. We are a small footwear startup (currently pre-launch) based in California. We have been working on our project for the last 4 years and have been completely self-funded. Having that experience and knowing how difficult it can be to get financing in countries without sound banking systems was the spark for our company creating this lending team.

Once we begin selling our footwear, we will be funneling a % of sales into our Kiva lending team. We call this the "Give a person a fishing pole" model. Different from the "1:1" model popularized by Toms Shoes, our model's goal is to give people the means to improve their lives and their future.

lenders.loan_because: mika umur 39, saya tinggal dengan istri di kota luwuk sulawesi tengah di rumah kontrak, sehari-hari saya bekerja sebagai tukang ojek yang penghasilannya hanya cukup untuk makan, motor yang saya gunakan tersebut dipinjam dari saudara. Sebelumnya saya bekerja sebagai karywan kontrak di beberapa perusahaan tapi kebanyakan banyak mengganggurnya dari pada bekerja. Oleh karena itu saya dan istri berkeinginan pulang kampung ke makale (toraja) provinsi sulawesi selatan untuk membuka sebuah toko kecil yang menjual barang barang kebutuhan pokok, dan kami mempunyai keinginan yang kuat untuk itu. Kami membutuhkan dana awal sekitar Rp. 50.000.000 untuk membeli barang-barang dan dijual kembali.
lenders.occupational_info: sebagai tukang ojek, mengambil penumpang dari satu tempat dan mengantarnya ke tempat tujuan dan dibayar sesuai tarif. Penghasilannnya tidak menentu

lenders.name: Olivia and Julien
lenders.loan_because: We loan because we want to help make the world a more awesome place for people and other living things.
lenders.occupational_info:
Olivia: We're siblings! I'm the older one. *whisper* I'm also the smarter one.

Julien: I heard that, bozo.

Olivia: That's the best name you can think of to call me? Bozo? You, sir, just proved my point about me being smarter.

Julien: Shut up.

Olivia: Hmm, let me think about that...

Julien: Fine then. Noogie!

Olivia: *dodges* Oh no you don't, prokaryote brain.

Julien: I challenge you to a duel! Get the paper towel tubes! En garde!

Olivia: You know, if we don't grow up soon, Mom and Dad are never going to let us stay home alone again.

Julien: True. But not growing up is too much fun!
